	   <tr><td colspan=2>Pretty good advice. I have a few cp to throw in though, if you don't mind.<br><br>When playing as an assist role, High Damage/Hgh Delay is preferable to High Damage/Low Delay. Less agro is involved (remember, you build agro on EVERY swing, you just build a bit more if you hit) and if you are using a 2hander, you do pretty decent damage, especially if your 2hs is maxed for your level. As an example, I can do over 100 points per hit at level 39+ with my 2hs maxed out at 200 and a Cystallized Two Handed Sword (24/49). My average is in the 40-50 range. pretty decent, you are whacking on the MoB, keeping up (for the most part) with the main tank's damage output except for the crits, and you can reaquire the MoB's attention with Spells and Taunt if you have to peel it off a caster real quick.<br><br>All in all, use your head, think fast and hit HARD when you hit! It also pays to be ready to swap your weapons out on a moment's notice if the situation changes.<br><br>Good luck, and may your arrows strike hard and true!<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
